You can simple define the JSON data in the single Javascript or Typescript file static and import that file directly inside your Javascript file.
I&#39;m assuming that you are using Angular and here is my example.

&gt;static-data.ts
```
export const data = {
   healthCare: {
      ...
   },
   banking: {
      ...
   },
   education: {
      ...
   }
}
```
Then in your component ts file, import this data.
```
...
import { data } from &#39;static-data&#39;;
...
```
Now you can use this data in your &quot;next&quot; button handler that might be defined in the component ts file.
&gt;e.g. with your example code, you can use this &#39;data&#39; variable inside your &#39;loadJSON&#39; function.

